==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: fire hydrant
<hw>fire hydrant</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>an upright hydrant that can
supply large volumes of water to use in fighting a fire. They are
commonly placed at intervals at the street edge of a sidewalk, spaced
for convenience in suppressing fires in towns.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fireplug, plug.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fireless</ent>⟦br⟧
